I want to help people. I want to work with children in trouble. I want to help families. I can help people in this way. I can show respect. I can help people make good choices. I want to learn more about helping people. This is important to me.

I have always wanted to help people. I did not know how I could help. I went to college. I saw people who had problems. I saw people who did not make good choices. I wanted to help. I went to college for four years. I liked to learn.

One day, I met a young man. A friend told me his story. He was afraid of his parents. They were mean to him. I wanted to help. I went to see his parents. I told them that I was worried about him. They did not seem happy. They said he was lying. I decided to be a social worker. I want to help children like this young man.

I believe in helping people. I believe everyone is special. We should not be the same. We should be different. I like to be different. I show people that I am different. I stand up for what is right. I fight for people who are treated badly. I will always do this.

This paper looks at sleep problems. It looks at two ideas: the body and how people live. The body idea looks at genes and health. The people idea looks at how the world around a person affects them. This paper looks at studies about sleep problems and how they match with these ideas. The paper also says what is good and bad about each study.  

Sleep problems can be many things. They can be a main problem. They can be from a mental health problem. They can also be from medicine or being sick. Main sleep problems are:

*  Trouble falling or staying asleep (insomnia)
*  Trouble waking up (hypersomnia)
*  Falling asleep suddenly (narcolepsy)
*  Breathing problems while sleeping

*  Problems with sleep time (circadian rhythm sleep disorder)

*  Other sleep problems

These are just main sleep problems.  There are also problems with actions in sleep. These are called parasomnias. They include bad dreams, sleep terrors, sleepwalking, and other sleep problems.

Sleep problems can also be from mental health problems. These problems are listed in two groups:

*  Mental health problems that affect how people feel (Axis I)
*  Mental health problems that affect personality (Axis II)


This paper looks at insomnia and sleep problems in general.  

The body idea looks at genes, how they are passed down, and how the body works. Tiny parts in the brain called neurons control sleep. These neurons have special parts called receptors. One type is called GABAB. This study looked at mice. It found that GABAB receptors help control sleep. When these receptors work well, people sleep better. If they don't work well, people have trouble sleeping. 

This study says that genes can affect sleep. If a person has a problem with their GABAB receptors, they may have trouble sleeping. This can make it hard to go to school, work, or do everyday things.

This paper talks about three parts of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, it says what CAPD is. Second, it talks about how doctors find CAPD. Third, it gives advice to teachers on how to help students with CAPD in school.

Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD), is a problem with how the brain uses sound. CAPD means the brain has trouble understanding sounds. People with CAPD can hear sounds, but their brain has trouble making sense of them. They may have trouble understanding words, especially when there is noise.

People first talked about CAPD in the 1950s. At that time, it was called "auditory imperception". Doctors found that some children had trouble understanding sounds even though they could hear.

CAPD can cause many problems. People with CAPD may have trouble:

* Hearing sounds in space.
* Telling the difference between sounds.
* Recognizing patterns in sounds.
* Understanding changes in sound, like sarcasm.
* Paying attention to one sound when there are many sounds.
* Understanding sounds in order.


To find CAPD, doctors look at how a person listens and does tests of their hearing. There is no one test for CAPD.

Twelfth Night say that disguise help trick people. But in the end, a person must be them self.  If not, they lose them self. It is hard to stop a trick because it can make people angry.

It is hard to trick people about being a man or woman. Why do people want to be someone they are not? In the play, Viola want to be a man to be safe. She say, "I will take you to a captain in this town/Where my girl’s clothes are, by whose help/I was saved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)

Viola is new in a new place. She wants to be safe. But now she is not with other women. She miss them. Also, Olivia think Viola is a man and fall in love. Olivia say, "Where are you going, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) Viola also like Orsino, but she can not say it. Orsino say, "Boy, you have said to me a thousand times/You should never love a woman like me.” (5.1. 260-261)

Twelfth Night show that tricks can help people see their true feelings. Olivia and Orsino like Viola/Cesario. But why? Do they like women? Or do they only like what Cesario looks like? Olivia change her mind fast. She likes Cesario one day and then Sebastian the next. She sees Viola as family, not a lover. Olivia say, "You are my sister.” (5.1.315)

German rule in Africa was harsh. This is clear from the way the Germans treated the Ovaherero and Nama people in German South West Africa. The Germans killed many of them.  

German rule in Africa was not all the same. Different places had different rules. This was true for schools too. When Britain took over German East Africa, they found many Africans who could read and write. German schools in other places were good.

South West Africa was different. The German government did not build many schools there. They let churches run most of the schools.  The government did help teach Europeans in South West Africa. They built schools and helped churches.

This made a big difference in South West Africa. Many Africans there could not read or write. This was not true in other German colonies.

This paper will look at why South West Africa was different. It will look at how people who lived there felt about Africans.

There are many books about schools in German Africa. Most are in German and were written a long time ago. Early books just described the schools. Later books compared schools in different places and looked at them in more detail.

One book looks at schools in South West Africa and East Africa. The book says that South West Africa had many people from Europe. This is why schools there were different.

South West Africa was not as hot as other places in Africa. There were many Europeans living there by 1913.

Popular music has many kinds of music. It is hard to list them all. Some kinds of music are rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk. Each kind has many smaller kinds. Heavy metal is one kind. It is popular now. It began forty years ago.

Heavy metal music has many different sounds. It can be loud and fast. It can also be sad and slow. People have made many kinds of heavy metal music. Some are very different from others.

Heavy metal is like a movement. It is more than just one kind of music. It is a way to feel and express things. Heavy metal music can be very strong. It can make people feel happy, sad, angry, or scared.

Heavy metal music uses loud guitars and drums. It often has dark lyrics. Some people think heavy metal music is about drugs. 

Heavy metal music came from earlier music. The Beatles made a song called "Helter Skelter." Some people think this song is the start of heavy metal music.

Henri Rousseau was a painter. He made dreamlike art before other artists did. His painting, *The Dream*, shows a woman in a dream. It shows Rousseau's dreams too. He wanted people to like his art. He wanted to be a good artist. 

Rousseau was born in France in 1844. He did not learn to paint in school. He worked for the government until he was forty. He then started to paint. He lost his wife and many children. He painted to feel better. Rousseau wanted people to see his art.

At the time, many good artists made art. Rousseau was not famous. He wanted to be like Matisse, a famous artist. Matisse made new art. Rousseau made art that looked old. He wanted to be liked by the art world.

Many smart people say that good ideas and good things are close to each other. They say that truth and beauty are the same. I agree. John Keats said that "Beauty is truth, truth beauty." That is all we know.

We learn many things in school. We learn things by doing. But we know what is good and what is beautiful without learning. Good and beautiful things are like stories. We do not tell people how to make good art or how to be good. We try to explain why art and actions are good.

We can talk about a painting. We can talk about colors and shapes. But we can not say why it is good. When we like a story or a painting, we often say, "There is something about it." We can not explain why we like it.

Art and good ideas can not be explained completely. Flannery O'Connor said that stories tell us things we can not say in other ways.

We feel good ideas and art in a deep way. We feel them, but we can not explain them. Literature is very good because it shows us good ideas.

Germany is a strong country. It has one culture. You can see this culture from the mountains of München to the city of Kiel by the Baltic Sea. The same culture is in Köln on the Rhine River, the center of Germany, and in the city of Dresden on the Elbe River. Germany has a special culture. This is because it came from many tribes.

Germania is the old name for Germany. People argue about where the name comes from. Tacitus, a writer, said the name came from a tribe called the Tungrians. This tribe was called Germans before they crossed the Rhine River to fight the Gauls. Julius Caesar, a Roman leader, first used the word “Germanus” to talk about people who fought against the Gauls. He used it to show the difference between the Gauls and the Germans. Some people think the word came from the Gauls. Caesar wrote about the Germans in his book about the Gallic Wars. He said, “Germans, who dwell beyond the Rhine, with whom they (The Gauls) are continually waging war.....They contend with the Germans in almost daily battles.”

Tacitus wrote a book about the Germans called “De Origine et situ Germanorum”. He said that the Germans were the first people in the land. He said they did not mix with other people. He said, “Who would leave Asia, or Africa, for Italy for Germany, with its wild country, its inclement skies, its sullen manners and aspect, unless indeed it were his home?

The Romans did not want to live in Germany. They went to Germany to get things and fight wars, but they mostly went home to their big empire. The Germanic tribes lived near the Roman Empire. They sold things and worked for the Romans.

I look down.  I see a brown thing in the toilet.  I feel strange. I think about art.  I think about a book. The book tells me how to see things. I want to be an artist. But this thing is hard to see.

When I was six years old, I wanted to draw.  I get a book about drawing. The book says to see a thing in a simple way.

I look at the brown thing. It is hard. I think about artists.  Picasso. Monet. They see things in colors. I want to see things in colors too. This is my start.

I pick up a mop.  I want to clean. The brown thing does not move. I push it again.  It is stuck. I feel bad.

I wrap the toilet paper around my hand. I look at the brown thing. I feel sad. I dip my hand in the water. I want to clean.

Teen drivers die many times. Many things cause this. The National Institutes of Health say the teen brain is not ready to drive. Teens also have little experience. This causes many accidents. Teen drivers have more accidents when they have friends in the car.  

The Southern California Injury Prevention Research Center did a study. The study showed young passengers cause more accidents. Some states try to make teen driving safer. They have rules for new teen drivers. New drivers can only drive for short times. They cannot have other young people in the car.

These rules are not enough. Young drivers are not ready to drive. Psychologist Marvin Zuckerman says 18 is too young to drive. He says young people like to take risks. They like to feel excitement. It is better to wait to drive until they are older. If we let young teens drive, more will die.

We need new rules for teen drivers. Schools can teach teens about driving. But no one under 18 can drive. New drivers can get a permit. They can also take lessons.

Many states require 6 hours of driving lessons and 50 hours of practice with an adult. We should have the same rules in all states. This will help keep teens safe.

I look at old movies from the Library of Congress. I like the trick movies. There are fifteen of them from 1895 to 1901. These movies use tricks to show things that are not real. I watch the movies and write about how they work.

Most trick movies are simple. They are made in a small room. The camera does not move. The actors only walk from side to side.

For example, in the movie "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel," the actors walk back and forth. The camera does not follow them.

The movies are also short. They are usually only one minute long. This is because each movie is one idea.

Some trick movies use many shots to make one idea. For example, in "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots," the movie shows Mary’s head being cut off. This is done by using many shots that are put together.

John Taylor from Carolina was early in his support for Republican ideas. He worked on a farm and had a short time in politics. This made him known for his strong beliefs about freedom and the government. He liked farming and thought it was the best way for people to live. This made him think about the government in a special way. He wanted to protect farming and make sure the government did not control it too much.

John Taylor thought the United States had a chance to make a perfect government. There were no old ways to stop them. This meant they could make a government where people ruled themselves. He believed people had natural rights that were important. If one right was taken away, all rights would be weaker. These rights should not be controlled by the government.

Taylor said that in the past, strong people hurt others. But in a good society, this should not happen. To make a good society, Taylor said the government had to be good and bad at the same time. He thought people were good and bad inside. He said, "Government is made by people, so it has good and bad parts too" (page 167). Taylor said good government protects people's things, helps farming, and does not let companies get too big. He thought that a good government would work well, even if the people in charge were selfish. He said people are always selfish, but this is bad only when it hurts others.

Taylor, like many other Republicans, wanted the government to follow the Constitution exactly. He wanted a small government with only the power given to it in the Constitution. He knew a big government was expensive and could be cruel. But he also said that just reading the words of the Constitution was not enough. You had to understand what the people who wrote it meant. Taylor said the Declaration of Independence was the most important document because it said the United States was made of separate states, not one big country.

Figure 17 show a big drop in commuter log write in the third month of the project. This was sad. It is hard to say why this happen. It is winter in New England. Fewer people ride bikes or walk to school. This may be part of the reason for the drop. December is the end of the fall school time. People are busy with schoolwork and grades. They may not think about the commuter log. December is also the time for holidays. School is closed for a long time. People do not need to come to school. Classes start again in late January. This may be why there are few logs in January also. But this does not explain why there are few logs in February.

Maybe the project started with a lot of excitement. This excitement may go down over time. To stop this, we had Carpool Challenge Week in March. This was a big effort to make people use the project again. It worked. More people wrote in the logs. One problem was keeping people interested in the project. There are school breaks and holidays. 

Another problem is that people like to drive. It is part of our culture. We need to give people a good reason to use other ways to travel. We gave out prizes. These were gift cards to places like restaurants, coffee shops, and stores. It would be good to see if bigger prizes would work. Maybe give away a bike, a car that uses less gas, or an electric car. This might help people use the project more. 

We did not change the prizes during the project. Maybe if we gave bigger prizes over time, more people would use the project. The gift cards were good at the start. But it might have been better to say we would give away bikes in December and a car in January.

An ETF is a way to buy many things at once. It is like a basket of things you can buy and sell on the market. An ETF can be like a basic group of things, like things in a store.

ETFs are good because they cost less than other ways to buy many things at once.  But you must pay a small fee each time you buy or sell an ETF.

There are many different kinds of ETFs, so you can buy an ETF for many different things. It is good to look at an ETF carefully before you buy it. 

We will look at one ETF called IHF.  We will look at the ten things inside IHF. We will see if these ten things are as good as buying IHF.  We will see if there are other ways to buy these ten things that are even better.

To do this, we will look at how much money you can make from each thing. We will also look at how risky each thing is. We will compare this to IHF.

We will see if it is better to buy IHF or to buy the ten things inside IHF.

Dream-land is one of Edgar Allan Poe's good poems. In "Dream-land", Poe use the word “Thulé”. This word is from Virgil. Virgil use the word for an island. The Greeks think this island is far away. It is sure that Virgil use the word. But there is another place where Poe may have seen this word. Poe like to read German books.

One writer, Karl J. Arndt, say that Poe copy from a German writer named Goethe. Arndt write a book about Poe and Goethe. He say that Poe's poem is like Goethe's poem. 

Goethe was a famous writer. He write a long poem called “Faust”.  "Faust" has two parts. One part came out in 1808. The second part came out in 1832 when Goethe die. In the second part of "Faust" is a short poem called “The King of Thulé”. 

This poem is about a king who is sad. His wife die. He drink too much. He miss his wife. He want to die. He give his things to his children. Then he go to a cliff. He throw a cup in the ocean. Then he close his eyes and die. 

The king in “The King of Thulé” is like the king in Poe's “Dream-land”.  They are both sad. They both like to drink. May be Poe was sad too.

Poe use the word “Thulé” twice in his books. He use it in “Dream-land” two times. He use it also in “The Pit and the Pendulum”.

We can read “The King of Thulé” and “Dream-land” together. They are like friends. The speaker in “Dream-land” talk about “Thulé”. He say it is dark and lonely. He see dead friends. This is like the king in “The King of Thulé”. He is alone and sad.


Poe like to read other writers. He like Tennyson. Goethe was important to Tennyson. So Poe may have read Goethe.

Under California law, can a customer get extra money because of being hurt in a store? The customer fell on some applesauce. The customer says the store manager was bad because he knew about the applesauce but did not clean it up.

A judge may not throw out the customer’s case. To get extra money, the customer must show the manager did something bad on purpose. The manager must have known the applesauce was dangerous.

The customer can say the manager knew it was dangerous because other people fell on spills before. The customer can also say the manager was bad because he did not care about the safety of his store. 

A worker told the manager about the applesauce spill at 5:00 pm. The manager said he was eating and did not have time. Another worker told the manager at 5:15 pm. The manager said the same thing. At 5:30 pm, the customer fell and was hurt.  Before the accident, five other people fell on spills in the store.

The customer is suing the store for money to pay for her hurt. She also wants extra money because the manager was bad.

In California, a person can get extra money if a store worker does something bad. The bad things are being unfair, lying, or being mean.

Four years ago, I took a class about Islam at CBC. We talked a lot about if Islam is a bad religion. This is still important today. After 9/11, the news showed Islam and Muslims in a bad way. Now, people are more kind to Islam in America. In 2001, a president could not have been named Barack Obama, who has Muslim family.

The story of Muhammad is interesting. The story says Muhammad was a good man, but history says he was not. I thought Muhammad made people join Islam by force. He took over groups and made them Muslim. But the story says Muhammad was a good man. People saw he was right and joined him.

The story of Muhammad is like the story of Jesus. Both men did miracles. Muhammad made food for many people. The story wants people to think Muhammad is a good man. It makes Jesus look less important. It is like they are copying Jesus.

The story also says many people joined Islam on their own. But the story tells us this from other people, not from the people who joined Islam. This makes the story less good.

The story makes Muhammad seem like a good man. But history says he was not. I think Muslims should know the real story about Muhammad.

Jesus say many things.  His ideas change how people think.  After Jesus die, people make new ideas about his teachings.  Christianity grow big.  But it change a lot.

Some people want to keep things the same.  They like the old ways.  But many want new things.  The world change fast.

In the future, more people learn about Jesus's real words.  They want to know what he mean.  They will want to take away things that people add later.

This will take time. It may be many years.  But Christianity will go back to the old ways.  People will follow Jesus's ideas more closely.  

This will make Christianity more alike everywhere.  There will be less fighting and more peace.

History show us this can happen.  People change.  Things change.

In the past, people hurt Christians. Now, Christianity is very strong.  

In the future, Christianity will go back to its roots.   It will be like Jesus's time. 

People will read Jesus's words in a new way. They will see them as stories and ideas, not just facts. 

Before Jesus, there was Judaism.  Judaism had many ideas about God.  These ideas became part of Christianity.

The Jungle show how people are greedy. They want good things for themself. They not care for other people. The Jungle show this with the factory owners. 

The owners want big factories. They do not care about people or the damage their factories make. The book say, "The line of the buildings stood clear-cut and black against the sky; here and there out of the mass rose the great chimneys, with the river of smoke streaming away to the end of the world". This show the pollution the factories make. The owners do not care about people or animals hurt by the pollution.

The owners also do not care about their workers. They want to make more money. They make workers work long hours. They fire workers without warning. Workers have no protection. The owners can make workers work in bad conditions. The book say, "So from the top to bottom the place is simply a seething cauldron of jealousies and hatreds; there is no loyalty or decency anywhere about it, there is no place in it where a man counted for anything against a dollar".

Workers have no help. Unions help, but they take money from workers. Workers are treated bad. They have no way out. The book say the workers are like slaves.

Many writers use different ways to make readers feel a certain way about things. Some are better than others. F. Scott Fitzgerald uses many ways in his book *The Great Gatsby*.  He sometimes pairs words that do not usually go together. He also uses symbols to make readers feel a certain way. Fitzgerald uses colors as symbols. He uses gold, green, white, gray, and red. In *The Great Gatsby*, Fitzgerald gives special meanings to white and gray and red and pink. He then uses these colors to make readers remember a feeling about important things.

Fitzgerald uses white and gray to mean sameness. White is better and more fancy. Gray is old and not as good. He shows this at the start of the book. Daisy and Jordan wear white all the time. Everyone wears white. Nick wears white clothes to Gatsby's party. Tom wears a white shirt when he meets Myrtle. Catherine is very white. The only time people are not in white is when Nick sees Gatsby's party. The party is full of bright colors. Fitzgerald uses white and gray to describe simple things. Nick goes to work in a white area of New York. The names of people at Gatsby's party are gray on Nick's list. Catherine lives in a white apartment building. Fitzgerald also uses white and gray to describe ordinary people and places. Daisy and Jordan had a white childhood. There are gray cars and gray land. A child in the train is gray. An old man selling dogs is gray.

After Fitzgerald uses white and gray a lot, he uses them to show that something is not important. He does this with Daisy. After a long time without using white or gray, Fitzgerald describes Daisy in white. Readers think of Daisy as less important. She is what Gatsby wants. Fitzgerald uses more white and gray to make Daisy seem less important. Her fur collar is gray. She is wearing white when Tom and Gatsby meet.

San Diego area have good farm land. The weather is warm and sunny. Farmers grow many things: tomatoes, citrus fruits, green leaves, squash, broccoli, herbs, peaches, lemons, berries, honey, and peppers. Many people want to buy food from farms that do not use chemicals. There are many groups in San Diego that help farmers grow food this way. They have long waiting lists. Eggs and milk from organic farms are also popular. Some organic farms let people visit. They can see how the food is grown. People can also walk, look at birds, and enjoy the farm. This helps the farmer make money and teach people about farming.

Organic farming is good for plants and animals. It does not use chemicals. But it cost more money. It need lots of work to keep pests away and to make the soil healthy.

Some things farmers do help animals, but they cost more money too. They plant special plants, move animals around, and remove bad plants. They also take care of plants so they grow in ways that help animals.


The farm is near a town called Potrero. It is a part of a plan to help animals and plants. This plan is still being made. It will help over one hundred kinds of plants and animals. Many are in danger of disappearing. Some are common now, but might be in danger soon.

Many years ago, people lived on this land. They raised cattle and cut wood. This land was given to a person who could farm it. They probably grew food for animals or cut wood. 

I found a farm in this area that is run organically. I looked at what the government can do to help small farms and make sure animals have a good place to live.

Culture is important in talks between people. Culture is how people live. It is not always easy to say what culture is. Culture is not the same for everyone. It is not one thing. People say things like, “All Russians are stubborn” or “All Japanese are nice.” These are not always true. It is better to know how culture can change talks.

When someone talks to people from another culture, they think about their own culture. They see things in a different way. 

Learning about another culture takes time. It means knowing the history of the people and what they believe. We should not judge other cultures. We should understand them. We should work with them. This is very important in talks.

Culture is not just about countries. Companies have their own cultures. Some companies work long hours. Some companies have relaxed times.  

We can see a company’s culture in how people dress and talk. We can see it in how work is shared. We can see it in how people are hired. Some companies help people give to charities. Other companies only help charities they choose.

American culture is different from company to company.  

Some cultures have many different parts. Other cultures seem the same. But there are always differences.

Values are important. Values tell us why people do things. If people value saving face, they will not be mean to others. If people value working hard, they will not give up easily. It is important to know these things before we talk to people.

The writer says that God does not exist. The writer uses a quote from the Bible to start.  This quote is from a book called Psalm 14.  Two writers, St. Anselm and Thomas Aquinas, talk about God.

The writer thinks that both writers believe in the same God.  The writer will look at both arguments.  The writer thinks that neither argument is very good.

The writer talks about St. Anselm first.  Anselm says that we can find God inside our minds.  He says that we know God exists.

The writer says that Anselm’s idea is like faith.  Faith is believing in something without proof.

The writer says that Thomas Aquinas has a different idea. Aquinas says that we can prove God exists. He says we can use reason and facts to know God exists.

Aquinas has five ideas about God.  He says that God exists because of changes, causes, things that happen, good things, and harmony. The writer says that Aquinas’s ideas are like a puzzle. We can know the puzzle piece is there even if we can’t see it.

A long time ago, a man was born. His name was Buddha. He grew up to be a prince. Buddha saw the sadness in the world. He left his home to learn about life. He learned about suffering.  He said that life has many problems. He said that people cause their own problems. He said that people can stop suffering. Buddha's words became a religion called Buddhism. 

Buddhism is very old. It has changed over time. People still practice it today. For example, in Sri Lanka, people have a special ceremony. Monks and regular people take part. It is called the water-cutting ceremony. Buddha did not teach about this ceremony. Still, it is important to people. Buddhism has changed a lot. It has changed inside and outside. Some changes were good, some were bad.

There are many words used to talk about these changes. Some changes come from inside Buddhism. Some come from outside. Some changes are good for Buddhism. Some are bad.  

Buddhists believe in three things: Buddha, the teachings, and the community. The teachings are in books. The books tell us about life and suffering. They say we can stop suffering by understanding. We can stop suffering by not wanting things. We can stop suffering by not being angry.

Buddhists also have rules. Regular people have five rules. Monks have many more. The most important rule is to understand the four truths. First, life is hard. Second, we cause our own problems. Third, we can stop our problems. Fourth, we can stop suffering by following the Buddha's teachings.

The United States and Mexico are two nations. They had a big fight for fifty-seven years. The fight went from 1836 to 1893. The biggest fight was the Mexican-American War. This war was from 1846 to 1848. The United States won the war. The United States took Texas and the American Southwest.

Many small fights happened after the war.  The fights stopped just before World War One. The fights began because the two countries had different ideas about religion, culture, and how to live. They also wanted the same things. This is like many other countries. Countries that live next to each other often fight.

David M. Pletcher said that the United States had big problems with Mexico and Cuba. He said this in 1977.  Mexico and Cuba are close to the United States. They fought with the United States. Other countries in Latin America had good relations with the United States.

Religion was a big problem.  Sally Frahm said this in 2001. She said that in the 1800s, Americans did not like Catholicism. They also did not like rulers who were kings and queens.  This is like the fight between the United States and the Soviet Union during the Cold War. Both fights were about ideas. But the fight between the United States and Mexico was about religion.

The United States and Mexico did not trust each other. They inherited this from their old rulers.  Spain ruled Mexico. England ruled the United States. This made it hard to be friends.  Diehl and Goerts said there were seventeen fights between the two countries. Most of these fights were about land. There were also problems with robbers from the border.

Fifteen years ago, I became sick. I did not know I was sick. I was a nurse. I liked to help people. When I was a child, I did not feel safe. So, I became a nurse.  "You will always have a job," people said. "People are always sick." I wanted to be a scientist or a writer. But I chose nursing. 

When I was 46 years old, I could not work. I am still sick. I get money from the government. I have no money saved. Every day is hard. I do not feel safe. 

I have no money. I have help from my family and some friends. I am strong, but when I am sick, I am not strong. 

There are always problems in life. You can plan, but you can't plan for everything.

I think the government is not good. It is not safe. Americans need to help each other. We need to trust each other. We need to ask for help.

Some people say that Americans are strong and indépendant. But the people who built this country helped each other. They shared food and helped each other.  People who traveled west helped each other.

Be ready for problems. Have a plan. But also know your neighbors.

Why do living things change over time? Are there limits to these changes? Even today, it is hard to describe the shapes of living things with math.  But math can help us understand how shells grow. A scientist named Raup and Stanley used math to study how mollusk shells change. 

This study looks at how math can help us understand how the shells of a type of mollusk called Prunum change over time. We used x-rays to look at the shapes of different Prunum shells. Then, we used a computer program to make new shell shapes.

A shell is like a tube that spirals. Each twist is called a whorl. The whorls are around a central line called the columella. The size of the whorls can change. The line between whorls is called a suture.

The biggest whorl is the last one. All the whorls except the last one make up the spire. The tip of the spire is the apex. The opposite end is the base.

We can look at shells from different angles. One common way is to look at the shell with the opening facing us.

To count whorls, look at the shell from the top. Find the first suture. Draw a line to divide the shell in half. Count the whorls from that line.

A shell grows by adding new parts. We can track the growth of the shell by looking at the center of each whorl.

We can use math to describe the growth of a shell. This can help us understand how shells change over time.

Indonesia's baby and child death rate stay the same for ten years.  Indonesia is doing good on some goals for help the world.  They are doing good on water and clean toilets.  But, they are not doing good enough to help mothers and babies.

Indonesia has more babies born with a doctor. Seventy-two percent of babies have a doctor. But, some doctors are not real doctors. They are helpers. These helpers can not help if there are problems. This makes the death rate for mothers high.

More babies are getting sick with diarrhea but not all are going to the doctor. We do not have enough information about mothers after they have a baby.

Cesarean births are low in Indonesia.  There are more cesarean births in cities. This means people in the country do not have good care.

Poor people have a hard time getting care. They do not have enough money.

We need to help babies and mothers. We need to help in the best way. Should we help with special programs or make the whole health system better?

Special programs are good because they are easy to plan. But, they can be bad. If we help too much in one area, other areas will get less help.

Many programs can make more work.

Victorian books are known for their close looks at detail and their focus on the rich people of that time. Two books that are from the Victorian time but are different are Oliver Twist and Wuthering Heights. Both books use mystery and strange things, which is not common in books from that time. This makes the people in the stories more interesting and helps us understand why they do the things they do.

Here is a part from Oliver Twist:

“Now, many confusing thoughts came into his mind. He thought he was still walking between Sikes and Crackit, who were angry and arguing. He could hear them talking. When he looked at himself, he saw he was talking to them…. Suddenly, he heard a loud noise like gun shots. People were shouting, lights flashed, and there was a lot of noise and chaos. It felt like someone was moving him quickly away. Through all these confusing things, he had a feeling of pain that was bad and made him feel sick.”  
(Dickens, 220)


The two books use mystery often through dreams or things that feel like dreams. In Oliver Twist, these strange things show us what is happening inside Oliver, what hurts him, and how he sees the world around him. When Oliver is shot, he remembers it in chapter 28 like a dream. He is trying to find help. This part shows how little control Oliver has over what happens to him, and how sick he is. He is seeing things, like Sikes and Crackit, because of the pain. The shooting is too much for him. He does not feel anything because he is in so much pain. He does not even notice the person who is taking him away. He feels his sadness again, but it is different now. The pain is constant and is connected to fear, not surprise. Because Oliver is so overwhelmed, we wonder who is responsible for his bad luck. It is not his fault. This shooting shows that Oliver has no control over anything. He can’t even try to stop bad things from happening, even when his life is in danger. This part also shows that Oliver is losing hope. It seems like Fagin is breaking him, making him accept his sadness. If Oliver was not broken, he would have tried to do something, even just to save himself.


“The day went by – day! There was no day; it was gone as soon as it came – and night came on again; night so long, and yet so short; long in its quiet silence and short in its passing hours.

A few years ago, I work in an after school program. I help young students. My best subjects are English and reading. A teacher ask me to help a boy named Adrian. He was in third or fourth grade. Adrian had big problems reading. I see that something was wrong. Adrian could say some letter sounds, other sounds, not so much. It was strange. Adrian speak perfect English, but he not know the English alphabet well. His mother came to the school one day. She only speak Spanish. I know a little Spanish. We talk. Then I understand. Adrian could read, but he did not know the English alphabet. I hope he is doing better now.

I tell this story about the language barrier in schools. We must help students who speak languages other than English. Reading is hard for some kids, even if they speak English well. We know this is a problem. What can we do?

One way is to teach in two languages. This helps all children, not just those who speak Spanish. Students in these programs do well in school. 

Some people worry that this will cost too much money. They say it will not help most children. This is not true. If we teach in two languages in all schools, all children will learn. 

How can we do this? We do not need all teachers to speak two languages. But we can have helpers who speak two languages.

We learn as children that some things are big, bigger than we can know. Some go to church, some to temple, some look inside. Many follow the beliefs of their parents. Some say there is nothing but what we can see and touch. Our ideas of what is important can change. We all look for meaning in life, a light to guide us.

My father said his favorite bird was a cardinal. We sat on the porch, rain falling on the roof. The rain made the plants wet. He looked at the rain, thinking hard. He was thinner now, his clothes loose. His hair was thin. He did not look at me. I felt sad, scared. I did not want to talk about missing him. I hugged him, sat close, and looked at the rain.

My father died in December, five days after my birthday. The medicine did not help him much, but he lived longer. I did not know why. I asked myself, “What kind of God would do this?” I did not pray. If God was real, he had stopped listening to me.

I did not want to watch him die. I did not want to see the life that made me end. I wanted to remember him as he lived. I knew him better than anyone else. I knew he did not want me to watch him die. I stayed in bed for days.

No one called me.

The "Gothic Novel" is old and new. It is a mix. Ian Watt says this in his book *The Rise of the Gothic Novel.* People say bad things about Gothic. They say it has no good ideas. They also say it is very good because it makes people feel strong emotions. The first Gothic Novel is *The Castle of Otranto* by Horace Walpole. He used old stories and new ways of writing. He made a new kind of story.  Gothic stories use old ideas from long ago. They use old buildings and stories. Even when *The Castle of Otranto* came out, the word "Gothic" meant many things. It was old and not as good as new things. But Gothic stories are still popular. They use old ideas in a new way. This makes them new again.

One idea in Gothic stories is Chivalry. Chivalry is about being a good knight. It is old. Walpole uses Chivalry to show what good people were like in the past. He thinks people today are not as good. Walpole wrote *The Castle of Otranto* when things were bad in his country. He was worried about the future. He thought people were not good anymore.  In his story, a man named Frederic is like a good knight. He is a prince. He is strong and brave. This shows that Walpole thought good people were lost.

Supply chain management is how goods move.  Goods go from a customer order to the customer. This includes raw materials, making the goods, and sending the goods to the customer.  The word "supply chain management" was first used in 1982 by Keith Oliver. He was a helper for businesses. Keith Oliver said the process helps companies give customers what they want quickly.

There are six important parts to supply chain management: making, getting supplies, storing, location, moving, and sharing information.  Business managers use these parts to help customers.

Making goods is the first part. It is very important.  Making goods is the start of the whole process. Managers need to know what customers want. They look at the market to see what people want. The market tells us what people want to buy.

Managers look at the market and learn what people want. Then they decide what to make and how much to make. They also decide where to make the goods. They want to make good quality goods and meet customer needs.

Managers also plan work and take care of machines. Making goods is very important.  If managers do not plan carefully, it can cost the company a lot of money.

The next part is getting supplies. Managers decide how to get the things they need to make goods. They might use different parts of their company or they might use other companies. This is called outsourcing. Companies do this to make things faster and cheaper.

Hitler is alive in Burma, the sign says.

Ellen Page, star of Juno, stand alone on a street. She hold a piece of cardboard. A message is on the cardboard. The message is strange. Burma is a country in Asia. It is ruled by a bad group. This group came to power a long time ago.

In 2007, people in Burma went to the streets to protest. Monks led the protests. They wore yellow robes. The protests were called “The Saffron Revolution”. At first, the government let the monks protest. But then, the protests became dangerous. The military attacked the monks.

Journalists were caught and put in jail. A Japanese journalist was killed. The government said that only a few people died. But a man who left the army said many more died.

This is not new. Governments try to stop people from speaking out against them. Roman emperors said they were chosen by gods. Japanese emperors are said to be gods.

One famous protest was in China in 1989. People protested the government. Many people died. Another example is the genocide in Rwanda. The government killed many people. Hitler also killed many people. He hated Jewish people.

Duke Ellington good at jazz. He make music for many years. He make music for his band. Ellington play piano, but he good at make music, too. He write music that make the band sound good. He write music for single musicians, and he write music for the whole band. He help the band sound new and good.

A book about music call Grove Music. It say Ellington good at use voice in music. He use voice like an instrument. A song called Creole Love Call show this.  Ellington use voice to make music sound different. He also make music that good for the musicians to play.

Creole Love Call a slow song. It have six parts.

Part one: Voice and woodwind instruments talk to each other. Voice start soft, then get strong.
Part two: Trumpet play a soft solo.
Part three: Clarinet play a high solo. Piano play soft music.
Part four: All the band play like part one.
Part five: Woodwind instruments play strong. Brass and drums play short sounds.
Part six: Voice and woodwind instruments talk to each other again. Voice sound like growl.

Ellington use voice in music. This good style for him.

Another song, Hot and Bothered, show Ellington’s skill. He make two musicians sound good together. One play trumpet, the other sing. Their music good because it sound different.

Ellington make another song, It Don’t Mean a Thing (If It Ain’t Got That Swing). He use a trumpet player, Joe Nanton, to make the music start.

She want something. This want no go away. It start when she be 14 years old. Now, she be 17. She want a person, not a thing. But she no like any boy. Some boy like her. They try to talk to her, but she no like them. She ask herself why. She think about it for many years. She have ideas, but no good ideas. She live her life and ask herself why she want this thing.

Her home life good. Her parents kind and calm. They no fight. They no fight with her much. They only fight about her wanting to be free. She from calm parents. But she fun and happy. People like her.

Today not a calm day. She walk in her house and look for something new. She hear a scream. It her mother's voice. She run to the kitchen. "Mom! Mom, what wrong?" Her mother on the ground. She say "Ow" many times.  Her daughter run to her. She put her hand on her mother. "Ouch ... sweet, I... need you to go to the hospital." Her mother say this fast. Her daughter know she in pain. "Okay Mom, tell me where to pick you up."  Her mother point. Her daughter happy she strong. She carry her mother to the car. She put her down and drive.

The hospital smell bad. It smell like sickness. But the daughter not think about this. She think about her mother. She carry her in and call for help. People come to help her mother. They put her on a bed and take her away. The daughter wait and worry.

Her mother fall from a high chair. She try to get a vase.

This study look at the link between a special diet and heart health. The diet is called the “Mediterranean Diet” or “aMed diet.”  People who eat this diet eat lots of fruits, vegetables, nuts, and fish.  They eat less meat and fat.

This study found that women who ate the aMed diet had less chance of heart problems. They also had less chance of dying from a stroke.

The study followed many women for twenty years. The women answered questions about what they ate each year. Doctors checked their health records. They found that women who ate the aMed diet lived healthier lives.

In two thousand seven, the United States had a big money problem. Many people lost their jobs. Homes were worth less. Many big companies had no money. This problem is still here. We must ask: how did this happen? How can we stop it?

This problem was made by people in government who made bad decisions. They put too much pressure on banks to give out loans to people who could not pay them back. This made the system weak. At the same time, two companies, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, were told to take these bad loans and make them into new things. When people could not pay back their loans, the banks had no money. They sold the bad loans to other people. This made the problem worse.

This problem started in nineteen ninety-nine. President Clinton wanted to be president again. He wanted to be popular. So, he made it easier for people to get loans. This made the problem worse. A reporter from the New York Times said that this was a bad idea. He said that the government would have to help again.

Many things made the problem worse. People got loans that changed price. These loans were put together with other loans and sold to many people. This made the problem bigger. People borrowed too much money for houses. When house prices fell, many people lost money.

Five big banks had a lot of bad loans. They lost a lot of money. Some banks closed. Others had to be helped by the government. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac lost a lot of money too. The government had to take control of them.

Exposition is tough. Many writers make this mistake. You must show, not tell. Dr. Merlin knows this, but she still sees bad exposition. It is like information overload. The reader gets tired.

Exposition is when you tell the reader what happened. It is like one person telling another lots of facts.  In a movie, this is called a "dump" of information. 

Let's look at an example. A story tells us that a woman met her husband. They were happy. He died. The story tells us this in two pages, but the husband and wife only speak a few times. This is bad exposition. The writer should show us how much the husband loves his wife. We should see this in his words and how he acts. We should see how the wife feels about him.

If the writer does this, the reader will feel sad when the husband dies. This will make the reader like the wife more.

In short, the writer must add details to the story. Do not just say things happened. Show us!

Sometimes writers want to skip over details. Maybe a new character was in the Air Force. Now they work at a gas station. They were married twice and have no children. They like to fish. They want to own the gas station. They had Eggs Benedict for breakfast.

Tell me more about this character!

I see two news cast from Columbus, Ohio. The first news was from NBC 4. It was live this morning. The big story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio. He hurt his wife. They did not say her name, but his name is Shad Hostettler. They showed a picture of him. He looks bad. They talk about this for two minutes. They said he hurt his wife many times. He is in jail now. I think they talk about this for a good amount of time.

The next story was about a man named Travis Buyers. He is 18 years old. Someone shot him early this morning. He is very hurt. No one is in jail yet. The police are looking for the person who did this. This story was short. I think that is because the man is black. I have noticed this before. When a black person is hurt, the news does not talk about it much. If a white person is hurt, the news talks about it a lot.

The next story was about a hole in a helicopter. Someone shot at the helicopter. The police think a small gun was used. The police are asking for money if someone tells them who shot the helicopter.

The next story was about the weather. It will rain on Saturday. It will be hot this weekend.

The news also talked about a robbery. A man robbed a store. He is black. He wore a black jacket. He is tall and heavy. The news talked a lot about his color.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez. He was in jail for selling drugs. He sold many drugs from Texas to Ohio. The news said he will be in jail for 300 months. I do not know why they said that. They also said he is Hispanic. I do not think this is important to the story.

Brothers have a strong link. This link is strong and never ends. Many things are in this link: love, pride, jealousy, and meanness. Brothers know each other better than any one else. They see themselves when they look at their brother. When things are bad, this link is very strong. It can be good or bad. When these feelings are clear, they are very strong.

Part of knowing these feelings is knowing the bad things that come with them. When you look a brother in the eye and see yourself in him, you see yourself as you really are. Not how others see you, but how you are inside. Your actions and the bad things that come from them show your true self.

In "The Scarlet Ibis" two brothers show this idea. They feel many strong feelings. In a beautiful place, they go on a trip that does not work. Sadness and pride fight in the end. Only one brother lives. The story shows these feelings through the brother Doodle and how he acts. It also shows these feelings through the narrator. The narrator shows how Doodle feels and sees the world.

Doodle's actions show one big feeling: pride. From the time he and Doodle go out together, to the end, the brother feels bad about Doodle. He wanted a brother who could learn things from him, like "holding my breath, running, jumping, or climbing the vines in Old Woman Swamp." He wanted a brother who could race with him and sit with him. But Doodle is weak. He was born with a weak heart. It was hard for him to do things. The brother was sad that his dreams were not real. He was even angry. He thought about killing Doodle. But then Doodle smiled at him. The brother felt happy. This shows that he really loved Doodle.

The human brain is very hard to understand. It is like a tool that works with information. Long ago, people said the brain was like a tablet, then a paper sheet, then a book. Now, some say it is like a computer. But these ideas are not perfect.

The brain takes in information from our senses. We feel things, hear sounds, and see light. The brain changes this information into signals.  Then, the brain looks at the signals in many ways. It looks at small parts and puts them together. It also uses what we already know to understand things faster.

For example, if we see a black box on white paper, the brain sees the shape and the color. It knows this is a box. Our brain also uses what we already know to help us see it is a box, not a hole.

The brain also decides what is important. It pays attention to some things and not others. We see many things, but the brain does not tell us about every one. We can hear our name in a loud room, but we do not hear every word.

The brain keeps information. It has different kinds of memory, like short-term and long-term.  First, information is stored. Then, it is kept for a short time or a long time.

There are many ideas about how the brain keeps information. Some ideas come from watching people remember things. Other ideas come from computers. Scientists also study the brain to learn how it works.

One idea is that the brain has parts that are like connections. These connections are for ideas. Ideas that are related are close together.

Aldous Huxley talk about the danger of new technology and the money system. He write about this in his book *Brave New World*. 

People in this book like to be together. They want to be happy. They are taught to think this way from when they are young. The people are like pieces in a big game. They follow one way of thinking. A leader, the World Controller, tells them what to do.

If we look at the book with the ideas of Karl Marx, we see that the book shows problems with the way money works. Marx talked about things like how people are the same and how things are treated as if they are more important than people.  This shows that Huxley was worried about these problems in his time.

Huxley uses Marx's ideas to show how the money system is not fair. The people who have money keep it from the people who do not. The people who have money do not want to share. They want to keep things for themselves. This is shown in the book. The people who work for the system (the Deltas and Gammas) do not have real power. They are taught to buy things, to spend money. The World Controller uses this to control them. 

The people who have power (the Alphas and Betas) know this is not fair but they do not do anything. They just accept their place.  The people in *Brave New World* do not have real relationships. They are not deep or interesting. This may be Huxley's way of saying that technology and money make people lose their freedom to think and feel. 

People in the book do not love each other. They do not feel strong emotions. They only talk about each other's looks. They are happy to do what they are told. This shows how money can make people lose their freedom.

I am a student at University Park. I have been here for two and a half years. For many students, moving around on campus is hard.  In my first year, I lived in East Halls. This is far from the center of campus. It takes a long time to walk to classes.

I talked to a student who went to school here before. The East Halls were far from the rest of the school. Now, there are new buildings and fields there. 

Our school is growing. This makes it harder to get around. What can we do?

Many students use bikes. But we also need more bike paths.

I have a friend who rides a bike again. He says bikes are good. They are the best way to travel. You can go far with just a little food and exercise.

I live off campus now. It is far from the center of campus. I bought a bike this year. It is good for me. I can get to class much faster. Bike paths are not always good. I have to ride on Pollock Road. It is not easy to ride on.

I like to walk too. But I am busy. If I did not have a bike, I would have to walk. It would take a lot of time.

In pursuing an education in social work, I intend to follow a career path with the Division of Family and Children Services to help children who have been abused or neglected; and to provide support for troubled families. Values that I can provide to the social work field include the following: service, respect, ethical nature, commitment to help improve relationships between others and to improve myself professionally to remain competent in my field. These core values are not just important to social workers; they are important to me personally. 

	I have always wanted to help others, but I was unsure of the career path that I wanted to follow. Throughout my years in high school and college, I saw many individuals flee from their problems in denial and a few used coping mechanisms that were less than ideal. Because of situations that I have witnessed, I chose to pursue a Bachelor’s degree in Psychology. Still unsure of a career path, I decided to take a break once I graduated from Piedmont College in 2009. One day that summer, I visited a friend who introduced me to a sixteen year-old boy sitting nervously on her couch. She explained to me why he was visiting: to escape his abusive parents. The next day, I learned that he had called the police to his parent’s residence. To see if I could help in any way, I drove over to his parents’ house. Once there, I privately explained my concerns to the police and told them I had just graduated with a degree in Psychology from Piedmont College. The police requested that I talk to the parents since there was nothing that the law could do for the teenager. When I questioned the parents about the situation, they seemed nervous and used excuses to describe their son’s “manipulative” behavior for involving outside sources to resolve “simple” disputes. After this particular experience, I began to seriously consider a career in social work to help children with “simple” disputes among family members.

	Another value that is important for the field of social work is social justice. As a society, we claim that the individual is important and we mourn those that we have lost. The concept of the “individual” that society holds is more a follower of archaic traditions than actual uniqueness. So, if society mourns lost individuals, then why do we strive to be similar to “everyone else?” I am an individual and do not enjoy placing limitations on myself to be similar to others. Throughout my years at high school and college, I protested against social injustice whenever I could: coloring my hair unnatural colors, wearing clothing that fit my personality, piercing my ears past the traditional set, declaring my involvement with GSBA (Gay Straight Bisexual Alliance), fighting against both racism and discrimination whenever I witnessed it, etc. I believe in social justice and I will continue to protest against social injustice.

The following paper addresses the Biological and Sociocultural models in relation to the disorder insomnia. The biological model focuses on genetic information that is inherited as well as medical aspects of health. The Sociocultural models look at environmental relationships and their applications to race, ethnicity, demographics, and socioeconomic status. The following review of insomnia looks at these models and explains each piece of research chosen to relate to and to better explain the models. The explanations of the research and their findings are then critiqued to mention their specific strengths and weaknesses.

A sleep disorder can be characterized as a primary sleep disorder, a sleep disorder related to another mental disorder, or a sleep disorder related to other issues. The Primary sleep disorders are Dyssonmias or Parasomnias while sleep disorders related to another mental disorder are related to an Axis I or Axis II disorder. Other categories of sleep disorders can be due to medical complications or the intake of a substance. The Dyssomnias are: Primary Insomnia, Primary Hypersomnia, Narcolepsy, Breathing- Related Sleep Disorder, Circadian Rhythm Sleep Disorder, and Dyssomnia Not Otherwise Specified (NOS). While Primary Insomnia is a complication in adequate or maintained sleep, Primary Hypersomnia is a difficulty in staying awake, both for at least a one month period of time. Narcolepsy involves cataplexy and/ or automatic REM. While Dyssonmias focus on initiating and remaining asleep, the Parasomnias are sleep disorders associated with behavioral abnormalities and/ or physiological occurrences. Parasomnias are Nightmare Disorder, Sleep Terror Disorder, Sleepwalking Disorder, and Parasomnias Not Otherwise Specified. The sleep disorders related to another mental disorder involve sleep difficulties due to Axis I (Clinical Disorders) or Axis II (Personality Disorders or Mental Retardation). The following review focuses on insomnia, and somewhat on primary sleep disorders in general in relation to the biological and sociocultural models.

	 The biological model of sleep disorders focuses on genes, heritable factors, and physiologically acquired aspect of sleep disorders. Neurons in the hypothalamus containing orexin are responsible for the regulation of sleep and wakefulness. This study experimented with mice and found that there are phenotypic GABAB receptors on the orexin neurons which are specifically responsible for sleep/ wake states. The activation of the GABAA receptor induces responses that promote sleep. If it is inhibited from firing, this can cause reduced anxiety and induce sleep. The GABAB agonist (baclofen) increased sleep time (Matsuki et al., 2009). Such results imply that the animal models of mice can be generalized to studies in humans. This shows that there is a genetic and environmental basis for the physical GABAB receptor in humans. A problem or absence with this receptor could alter the ability of one to have adequate sleep without medication. The sociocultural implication of this study is that if the phenotype was inherited, this could regulate sleep, and an alteration of the receptor would naturally disturb sleep for an individual. This would negatively impact aspects of life such as school, career, and every day events that involve monotonous tasks and focus.

This paper covers three areas of Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD). First, a brief definition of the disorder is provided. Next, diagnosis is explained, with common characteristics, or “red flags”. Finally, the paper concludes with ways that a teacher in a mainstreamed classroom environment can assist a student with CAPD.

	Central Auditory Processing Disorder (CAPD), or Auditory Processing Disorder (APD) “refers to the efficiency and effectiveness by which the central nervous system (CNS) utilizes auditory information. Narrowly defined, (C)AP refers to the perceptual processing of auditory information in the CNS and the neurobiologic activity that underlies that processing and gives rise to electrophysiologic auditory potentials” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005), meaning it is a disorder wherein the central nervous system (i.e. the brain) cannot properly process things that are heard. People with CAPD can hear normally, and are therefore not considered “hearing impaired”; rather, the area of the brain that translates what we hear, separating words or differentiating conversation from background noise does not function as it typically should. 

	The earliest mention of the disorder that became CAPD is from the mid-1950s, called “auditory imperception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005) when researchers were evaluating children with communicative disorders. The Italian research team of Bocca, Calearo, and Cassinari began developing tests for these children in 1954; in 1961, Kimura “introduced dichotic testing and formulated a model to explain the physiology of the CANS underlying dichotic perception” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). A national conference was held in 1977 that stimulated research on children with CAPD. 

	CAPD manifests itself in multiple ways: the person suffering may not be able to localize or hear sound in space; may have difficulty discriminating between two or more “acoustic events” (sound occurrences); may not be able to recognize sound patterns; may not be able to differentiate changes in speech (like detecting sarcasm based on change of voice); one sound may be blocked by a subsequent sound; may not have the ability to synthesize sound clues (that is, interpret in a meaningful way that they can then act upon); and may not be able to determine the sequence in which auditory information is presented (Ferre).

	In order to diagnose CAPD, the patient must be screened with “systematic observation of listening behavior and/or performance on tests of auditory function”, which may be conducted by “audiologists, SLPs, psychologists, and others using a variety of measures that evaluate auditory-related skills” (American Speech-Language-Hearing Association, 2005). This may include questionnaires and surveys, observation of auditory behaviors, including how the patient responds to certain stimuli. There is, at this time, no one tool or test that is used consistently to a high rate of diagnostic success, and there is no known cause for the disorder. Many tests used present the patient with multiple, simultaneous auditory stimuli and then ask for them to differentiate certain items, like a series of words or numbers. More advanced tests include recording acoustic signals within the ear and measuring the responses to the signals.

The play Twelfth Night seems to say that although disguise is in fact useful in perpetrating long bouts of deception, in the end a person must reject that newly formed guise, or else risk losing themselves forever in the process. A big problem with ending a deception, however, is that one may find themselves alienated in the process. Therefore, in the end, one must decide between one’s own self preservation, or the preservation of relationships with those around them. For although some will respond neutrally to discovering that they’ve been tricked, still others will not take the deception so lightly, and will be likely be offended by the whole charade.
The topic of deception in gender role reversal is especially problematic, because it brings up many side issues, perhaps the most important one being, why? Why does the subject feel the need to shirk their own identity and take up a disguise in the form of the opposite gender? In Viola’s case, it is obviously a form of self protection.: “I’ll bring you to a captain in this town/ Where lie my maiden weeds, by whose gentle help/ I was preserved to serve this noble count…” (5.1.247-249)
Having newly arrived in a foreign land, Viola feels it necessary to pretend to be a man to protect herself from would be attackers. Viola’s plan works, but it also alienates her from the women around her, cutting her off from an important support system. To make matters worse, she is apparently so convincing at appearing to be a man that Olivia confuses her with Sebastian, and in effect falls in love with her. “Whither, my lord? Cesario, husband, stay.” (5.1.138) On top of that, she also has to deal with suppressed romantic desires between her and Orsino: “Boy, thou hast said to me a thousand times/ Thou never shouldst love woman like to me.” (5.1. 260-261)
Although this may be a somewhat progressive attitude, to the modern reader, Twelfth Night may be seen as an illustration of how deception may help facilitate the unveiling of suppressed emotions, especially in the cases of Olivia and Orsino. Certain passages seem to hint that the aforesaid characters may have unexpressed subconscious desires that the appearance of Viola/Cesario forces them to deal with. For instance, is Olivia attracted to Cesario because Cesario appears to be a man, or does Olivia really secretly harbor feelings for women? One would argue that this is probably not the case, because Shakespeare’s character Olivia seems more likely to be parodying those people of his time period who judge others only upon their looks. 
This is evidenced by the ease with which Olivia switches her romantic ardors from Cesario to Sebastian, and begins to regard Cesario/Viola as family rather than a love interest: “A sister, you are she.” (5.1.315)

German colonial rule has been noted by various observers for its brutality, notably with respect to the genocide of the Ovaherero and Nama in German South West Africa. Of course nothing so broad as an entire colonial empire can be accounted for by such a simple description. The German colonial empire was as varied in policies and ruling style as it was in geography. Educational provision across the colonies was similarly diverse. When the British took over German East Africa (Tanganyika) in 1919, they found a large population of educated and literate Africans. German educational efforts in Kamerun and other colonies were also praised by contemporary authors. 
The situation in South West Africa (present-day Namibia) presented a stark contrast.  Unlike in East Africa, where the government established state schools and played a prominent role in the education of the natives, in South West Africa the task of native education was left almost entirely to missionary societies that received limited government support. The government did however invest significant resources towards the education of Europeans in the colony, establishing s system of state schools as well as more heavily supporting and regulating missionary schools. These educational policies had longstanding effects on South West Africa, even after German rule. While other German colonies boasted significant numbers of literate and educated Africans, in South West Africa “the overwhelming majority of the population remained untouched, uneducated, and illiterate.” Various social, political, and economic factors led to the divergent experience of South West Africa. This paper seeks to expand the discussion by identifying these factors and paying particular attention to new research on the attitudes of settlers and colonial authorities to native Africans.
There is a wealth of literature dealing with education in the German colonial empire specifically. Most of these sources are in German and were written in the early twentieth century, during or shortly after the period of German colonial rule. The aim of early works was primarily to describe the features of educational systems in these colonies. Later writings in English expanded the discourse through comparative studies of education in the various German colonies and more detailed analyses of specific aspects of education. These studies illustrated significant differences in the educational systems of different colonies. The most prominent work to explicitly address the topic of this paper is Cohen’s study of education in South West Africa and East Africa. Cohen compares the educational systems of the two colonies and discusses the factors that account for the differences between them. According to Cohen, the large settler population of South West Africa explains many of the distinguishing aspects of the colony’s educational system.
Compared to Germany’s other colonial possessions, South West Africa had a moderately temperate climate, although much of the territory is covered by arid desert. The European population of South West Africa reflected the relatively hospitable conditions. By 1913 nearly 15,000 whites lived in South West Africa, while only 5,336 lived in the colony with the next largest settler population, East Africa.

‎	‏The classification of Popular Music has grown over the past‭ ‬100‭ ‬years to include so many genres that it is difficult to definitively list them all. Complicating matters,‭ ‬most if not all genres—rap,‭ ‬rock,‭ ‬country,‭ ‬jazz,‭ ‬folk,‭ ‬just to name a few—have spawned multiple sub and sub-sub genres within their domain.  Arguably the sub-genre of Heavy Metal rock has become one of the most diverse and expressive genres of all popular music in the past‭ ‬40‭ ‬years. It is expressive because it displays a wide range of emotions,‭ ‬although they tend to lean toward the darker side of the spectrum. It is diverse in that quite soon after the beginnings of the genre,‭ ‬people started to realize that it had real flexibility and started to take advantage of it to create their own sub-genre,‭ ‬which then was followed by sub-sub-genres,‭ ‬and the chain continues until today. 

Today we have reached a point in the heavy metal movement where there are so many niches of groups that it is hard to determine what exactly heavy metal is. It has grown to incorporate so many themes from other genres,‭ ‬but like everything else,‭ ‬it spawned from somewhere. In order to properly understand the metal music that exists everywhere today,‭ ‬one must first understand what the metal movement is,‭ ‬and why it’s a movement rather than just a genre.

‎	‏Metal is,‭ ‬in many ways,‭ ‬a movement defined by darkness. Metal can be considered a‭ “‬music of more‭”—‬more bass,‭ ‬more volume,‭ ‬more violence,‭ ‬more theatricality. Less primitivism,‭ ‬more chops‭; ‬people in metal bands really know how to play their instrument,‭ ‬and it comes through in the music. Metal is also—although it may not come as a surprise—a movement that is heavily drug induced. There was a psychedelic drug boom in the mid-70‭’‬s that led to people getting crazier,‭ ‬leading to them to make crazy,‭ ‬other-worldly records,‭ ‬using the drugs as a scapegoat for their creation. It possesses many dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities,‭ ‬which was very new to the music scene because a large amount of popular music had qualities that weren’t true to the darker side of the emotional spectrum. Also,‭ ‬later generations of metal have taken some of their influence from the dark,‭ ‬visceral qualities that were so present in the Romantic Era. Lyrics such as the following express the darkness that is such a staple of the movement:‭ (‬Byrne‭)‬


	
These lyrics from Helter Skelter display the darker side of the Beatles. It exhibits an up and down,‭ ‬supposedly that of drugs. This song is considered by some to be one of the first Heavy Metal songs. It was a response to a Rolling Stones song that was also on the heavier,‭ ‬darker side.
